1 4. If a coach reasonably believes a student is exhibiting symptoms or warning signs of
2 sudden cardiac arrest, the coach may remove the student from participation in an
3 athletic activity. If the student is removed from the athletic activity, the coach shall
4 attempt to notify the student's parent or legal guardian.
5 5. A student who is removed from participation in an athletic activity under subsection 4
6 may not participate in an athletic activity until the student has been evaluated by and
7 received written clearance from a licensed physician, physician assistant, or nurse
8 practitioner.
9 6. The sponsor of a recreational youth athletic activity may follow the guidelines provided
10 under this section.
